name.text: "IT'S THRIFT!" Pop-Up Thrift Workshop
name.html: "IT'S THRIFT!" Pop-Up Thrift Workshop

description.text:
If you’ve ever wanted to master the art of thrifting, get ready for “IT’S THRIFT!” — A Curated Pop-Up Thrift Workshop. In this 90min. two-part workshop, you’ll get the essential tools to implement when thrifting, along with a LIVE personal hands-on thrifting experience!
Part I — Info Session
First, I’ll share the exact methods I use to save hundreds of dollars each year on my wardrobe, and how to come out with fab finds every single time when thrifting!
Part II — Hands On
Lyft transportation will then be provided to the nearest thrift store, where you’ll get to apply everything you learned in the Info Session! Here, you’ll get personal direction and guidance from me, along with FREE consulting on your thrift finds!
You’ll walk away from this workshop knowing how to . .


Best prepare for thrifting.


Find the best thrift shops.


Identify key deciding factors.


Get the perfect fit.


Quickly get in and out.


Utilize additional discounts.


Find the best value pieces.


Maximize the wear from your thrift finds and your overall wardrobe.


Whether you’re new to thrifting or a serial thrifter like myself, this workshop will provide you with valuable information and hands-on actionable steps to last you a lifetime! Save yourself the time, money and frustration and register today!
 
FAQs 
Can I bring someone with me?
As there is limited space, no additional guests are permitted.
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Feel free to email us at hello@jeimonroe.com 
What's the refund policy?
All registrations for workshops are non-refundable, but are transferrable to a new workshop date or time. To reschedule a workshop, please contact us at hello@jeimonroe.com.

name.text: Queen Space: Jewelry Pop-Up and Healing Circle
name.html: Queen Space: Jewelry Pop-Up and Healing Circle

description.text:
Hey Queens! Need an excuse to dress up and celebrate your best life while healing and releasing with other Queens? Join myself and friends for a gathering in an intimate space in Brooklyn, NY for The Queen Space Day Party and Rose Quartz/Love inspired Healing/Sharing Circle!!! We are excited to get together, release and flick it up again with more beautiful Queens.
Join our chill experience to unwind from the week and feel like the Queens you are. I, @reignglobal will be hosting and selling my Custom Crystal Crowns and Jewels! Come enjoy the libations, music and adornment in my heavenly space that means so much to me with good energy. This is the perfect time to speak one on one with me about healing, crystals, love, life....ANYTHING. I have been connecting with so many beautiful Queens who do amazing things and I would love to bring you all together again! This space is a growing family and I can not wait to see who joins us! A nice assortment of wine, cacao, and vegan food will be provided!
From 1p.m-3p.m will be the time for all of the queens to mingle..get to know each other, eat, sip and purchase healing crystals crowns/jewels and 3p.m-3:30p.m will be the Cacao Ceremony lead by @manifestyoursoul and 3:30-6 will be the healing circle! @manifestyoursoul will ALSO be doing sacred intuitive face paint 
LOCATION: Brooklyn, NY. You will receive the location when you purchase your ticket closer to the event so we can keep the space sacred.
ATTIRE: Since this event is inpired by love we will be honoring Rose Quartz and the dress code is all things Pink/Gold/Champagne/Tan to bring out the energy of love and royalty!
Parking?
There is parking in the neighborhood if you are driving. Uber/Lyft and the J to Halsey stop (20 minutes from Manhattan) works as well.
Are there ID or minimum age requirements to enter the event?
Age Requirement 18 and over
What can I bring into the event?
Your beautiful self and golden energy!
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
info@palaisapiim.com

The second of the Series of HCCC Foundation Pop-up Dining events will be held on Friday, February 8  at 7 p.m. in the College’s Culinary Conference Center at 161 Newkirk Street in Jersey City.
The cost of $75 per person includes a five-course meal with wine pairings.
Proceeds provide scholarships to deserving HCCC students.
Reservations are a must.
For more information contact Mirta Sanchez, Assistant to the Vice President for Planning and Development
(201) 360-4004    -    msanchez@hccc.edu
 
FAQs
 Is my registration fee or ticket transferrable?
Yes. If you are unable to attend, please contact msanchez@hccc.edu to inform who will be coming in your place.

No. There will be a list with names of attendees at the door.
 What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Street parking is easy to find at that time.  There is also a Parking Garage accross from the Conference Center.

name.text: Flying University: Reagan, Pop Art, the Alt Right - Oh My!
name.html: Flying University: Reagan, Pop Art, the Alt Right - Oh My!

description.text:
Border walls. Comic Books. Raeganomics. Pop Music. The Alt Right. POC. Trump. What do they all have in common? 
Join us as we take a trip back to the 80s and Ronald Reagan’s presidency to reveal how that pivotal White House win birthed a whole new generation of artists & pop culture - and arguably helped produced today’s far-right republicans and the inevitable Trump Administration.  Our keynote speaker for the evening will be Prof. Jonathan Gray, joined by our TA - illustrator and filmmaker, Jason Scott Jones.
 
Doors 6:30pm / Show 7:00pm Tickets: $15 adv / $20 door 21+
 
Flying University is a crash course in hidden histories - shining a light on ideas, people, science, and moments in history from a new perspective.  It’s an interactive presentation series featuring storytellers, experts, professors, comedians, (and of course, drinking).  Our speakeasy-style lectures were conceived in the spirit of the underground university in Russian-occupied Poland by the same namesake, which taught subjects and students banned by the state-run schools.  This historical rebel organization educated women and other marginalized groups who were barred from attending the official Polish universities. Caveat's Flying University carries on the mantle, sharing stories by and about communities whose stories are often untold. (Hosted & produced by Chinisha S.)
Jason Scott Jones is an illustrator, motion graphics designer, and filmmaker who has worked with some of the top media companies in the industry, including DC Comics, NBC, CBS, Time, Inc. and many more.
Jonathan W. Gray in an Associate Professor of English at the CUNY Graduate Center and John Jay College, whose works focus on post-WWII American culture, African American literary production, popular culture, comic books, graphic novels, and others narratives of visual culture. His first book, Civil Rights in the White Literary Imagination (Mississippi) traces the white literary responses to the period between the Brown case and the death of Martin Luther King.  His forthcoming project, Illustrating the Race (Columbia), investigates how the twin understandings of illustration—the creative act of depiction and the political act of bringing forth for public consideration—function in the representation of African Americans in comics and graphic narratives published since 1966. 
 
 
REFUND POLICY: Tickets maybe be refunded up to 24 hours before the event. Within 24 hours we may take exchanges for other events at our discretion. No refunds after the event.

name.text: La Vie En Rose: AN ELEGANT  BLEND OF AMERICAN JAZZ, FRENCH CHANSON & POP
name.html: La Vie En Rose: AN ELEGANT  BLEND OF AMERICAN JAZZ, FRENCH CHANSON & POP

description.text:
Jazz-influenced French indie singer/songwriter Violette comes to Club Bonafide in New York City. Born in Paris and raised in a small village on an island off the French Atlantic Coast, and now making her home in Brooklyn, Violette has clearly been influenced by such French luminaries as Jacques Brel and Edith Piaf, but Ella Fitzgerald, Stevie Wonder and Michael Jackson have also had a hand in the development of her sophisticated pop sound. Her most recent album, 2014’s Falling Strong, showcases a collection of originals that, although rooted in jazz, reflect the young artist’s eclectic range of influences from pop to rock and R&B. name.text: NYFW 8th GOLDEN KIDS RUNWAY, Fashion fights for a Cause
name.html: NYFW 8th GOLDEN KIDS RUNWAY, Fashion fights for a Cause

description.text:
Golden Kids Runway, Fashion fights for a Cause is hosting 8th Annual Golden Kids  Runway, Fashion fights for a Cause benefiting Sickle Cell Awareness.

In celebrating the world of fashion for kids. Golden Kids hold the key to a brighter, stronger more inclusive, golden society. We want to inspire children to always Shine, Dream Big, Unite & Rejoice in diversity, confidence, love and infinite potential. 
Golden Kids Runway – Fashion Fights for a Cause (GKR – FFC) encapsulates an eclectic blend of child models, trendy music, talented performances, whimsical clothing with tremendous amounts of positive energy. What makes GKR – FFC unique?  It’s for the kids, by the kids!  The hosts, DJ, performers, and production support are children who donate their time and efforts all for a worthy cause.
Golden Kids  Runway, is a new Fashion Show event featuring various designers and boutiques trendy fashions. Also,  Mass media, bloggers, social networking outlets,  specialty retail buyers,fashion industry representatives and corporate sponsors & influences are sure to enjoy this children's fashion & art industry's premier event.

name.text: Soloicity
name.html: Soloicity

description.text:
METROPOLIS ENSEMBLE PRESENTS
SOLOICITY
a night of composer-performer sets with styles ranging from folk to pop to experimental, as part of Molly Joyce’s Light series with Metropolis Ensemble



Molly Joyce’s Light series with Metropolis Ensemble concludes with a night of composer-performer sets, with styles ranging from folk to pop to experimental, and seemingly everything in-between. Composer/performers include Lea Bertucci, Carla Canales, Margaret Davis, Liz Faure, Sarah Goldfeather, Molly Joyce, Anna Meadors, Angélica Negrón, and Emily Wells.


Doors open at 6:30pm, show at 7:00pm.Because of the generous support of our followers, Metropolis Ensemble is thrilled to offer our pop-up venue at 1 Rivington as a place for new projects and works of music to take shape, at little to no cost to our artists. Select artists are given the opportunity not only to share finished works, but to use this platform to craft ideas into tangible realities.

name.text: FREE FIFI FASHION WEEK SHOW - INDEPENDENT FASHION DESIGNERS
name.html: FREE FIFI FASHION WEEK SHOW - INDEPENDENT FASHION DESIGNERS

description.text: This is your personal invitation to FIFI Fashion Week.  FIFI - Fashion Industry Finest Independent Designers Fashion Week features Independent Designers making an impact on the Fashion Community.  The show will be held at The Watson Hotel 440 West 57th Street, Embassy Ballroom, NYC 10019, FIFI  FW will feature a Pop Up Live Mannequin Boutique where the public can purchase designer garments and accessories, some as low as $40.  The Pop Up Live Mannequin Boutique will run from 12Noon - 2:30pm (visit on your lunch hour and come back for the show)  and the Runway Show will start at 7:00pm, one FREE ticket gets you in both. Seating assignments will be given out on a first come first seated bases starting at 4:30pm.  Doors will open for people with seating assignments at 5:30pm, once the seating is finished, the standing are let in.  From 5:30-6:30pm we have Front Row, Red Carpet and Runway photos and interviews.  The show starts at exactly 7:00pm.  After the show, the public can take photos on the Red Carpet and revisit the Pop Up Boutique to get a close up look of the designers garments and purchase or place an order.  The entire purpose of the show is to give independent fashion industry talent an opportunity to expand their customer base.  We hope you will mark your calendars to attend both the Pop Up Boutique and the Runway show, you will have a great time.  May I suggest you arrive early to get your seating assignment as seating is limited.  NOTE: People that visit the Pop Up Live Mannequin Boutique between 12Noon and 2:30pm, can get their seating assignment for the Runway show but must be in line when the doors open for the seating assignment to be honored.  If you arrive after 5:30pm your seat will not be honored.  We look forward to seeing you at the show.

name.text: Conception Art Show - New York City
name.html: Conception Art Show - New York City

description.text:
You are invited to attend Conception Art Show. A "pop-up" event presenting the work of 40 local artists. Featuring DJ, complimentary appetizer hour, and a cash bar. Guests will have the opportunity to purchase something original for their home or workplace without incurring a gallery commission.
The immersive exhibit, active in 12 cities around the U.S. is the brainchild of New York City Business Journals, “2016 Woman of Influence,” Rachel Wilkins. The organization, founded in 2011 in NYC, hosts one-night 'pop-up' art events in 12 cities around the U.S. while additionally providing guidance and support for artists and makers looking to sell or promote their work, both online and in person. "Bringing art to life in a way you can truly connect with is paramount to us here at Conception." - Conception Arts Co-founder, Rachel Wilkins explains.
"There are few other opportunities like this. The environment is unique and the art is wonderful" - Dallas Style & Design Magazine (September 2017 Issue)
"Must See" - Paper Magazine (2015)

name.text: Babetown Singles
name.html: Babetown Singles

description.text:
Love is in the air in Babetown, babes and this year we celebrate with our first ever Babetown Singles.  Join us for an evening in a beautiful Williamsburg home of hearty bites and indulegent chocolate desserts, sparkling wine and creative mocktails.  Plus, at this extra flirty Babetown, we'll have fun colored wristbands and other little ice breakers hidden through out the home.  Get out of the cold, bbys and enjoy a home cooked meal made by and for all that mid winter love.  
Babetown is a pop up supper club for queer women, trans and non binary people that meets in a series of private homes. We offer our guests a relaxed environment, with a full dinner and drinks, in which to talk with each other, eat with other and connect with each other.

name.text: Cardio Ballet
name.html: Cardio Ballet

description.text:
Try your first class at The Ballet Spot for FREE! No prior dance experience is required.
Ballet dancers take a ballet class as their workout, and now, so can you!Our signature Cardio Ballet Workout is a revamp of traditional dance-fitness: Rather than hip-hop and jazz as its basis, this class is ballet. The instructor will dance with you the entire time and guide you step by step through a full-body warm up and dances across the floor. The class is choreographed to piano renditions of inspiring pop, rock, and Broadway music, so you will feel uplifted to keep moving, learning, and definitely sweating!
Appropriate attire is exercise clothes and regular socks, sticky socks, or ballet slippers. Need slippers? Come early and borrow a pair from us!

name.text: Sabar
name.html: Sabar

description.text:
With live drumming. Express yourself with the fun, energetic movements of this upbeat dance from Senegal that is often performed at celebrations like weddings, baby naming ceremonies, and other happy occasions. The class starts off with a dynamic warm-up that incorporates Sabar technique, and then moves into choreography that will have you popping your lapa (wrap skirt) across the dance floor.
 
Lamine Thiam            




Lamine is a world-renowned dancer, choreographer, drummer and actor, and specializes in West African Dance from his native Senegal and neighboring countries, including rhythms such as Sabar, Djembe and Bougarrabou. He has graced the stage at venues worldwide including Carnegie Hall, Symphony Space, The United Nations and Lincoln Center (NY), as well as theaters in Japan, Germany, London, Mexico and the Caribbean.
Lamine is happy to be back in New York, bringing love to his Sabar students!

name.text: Judy Garland LIVE In Concert - The Songs That Got Away - starring Peter Mac
name.html: Judy Garland LIVE In Concert - The Songs That Got Away - starring Peter Mac

description.text:
Judy Garland LIVE In Concert - The Songs That Got Away - starring Peter Mac as Judy Garland 
Here's a chance to take another trip over the rainbow with everyone's favorite diva, Judy Garland! In a new cabaret concert specifically designed for the Grand Theatre inside the Producers Club in New York City. The evening is crafted through a sparkling selection of songs that Ms. Garland (herself) never had the chance to sing both during and after her lifetime. Expect the unexpected. ABBA, Disney, Sondheim, pop standards and more! 
The show takes place in an intimate cabaret theatre where Peter Mac as Judy Garland warms up the winter by once again demonstrating his acclaimed ability to recapture the magic, the humor, and joy of the woman who was unhesitatingly billed, reviewed and accepted as "the world's greatest entertainer." 
There is no minimum.  However, there is a full bar and you may bring drinks back to your seat to enjoy during the performance.
